1
00:00:00,500 --> 00:00:03,100
<i> A huge "thank you"!</i>

2
00:00:03,267 --> 00:00:04,833
<i> For the Philippine snow?</i>

3
00:00:04,967 --> 00:00:08,267
For reminding me that there are
<i> other reasons to be happy.</i>

4
00:00:08,400 --> 00:00:10,500
<i> You're welcome!</i>

5
00:00:10,633 --> 00:00:12,000
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

6
00:00:12,133 --> 00:00:14,400
<i> We've forgiven you, Luna.</i>

7
00:00:14,533 --> 00:00:17,700
<i>We hope you can
forgive yourself, too.</i>

8
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:19,500
<i> They probably took Juan here!</i>

9
00:00:19,633 --> 00:00:21,067
<i> We're not sure about that.</i>

10
00:00:21,200 --> 00:00:22,900
<i> What if it's just a safehouse?</i>

11
00:00:23,033 --> 00:00:24,533
<i>So, what's next?
What are we going to do?</i>

12
00:00:24,667 --> 00:00:26,500
<i>Should we go home
or get caught?</i>

13
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:28,300
<i>- Let's go.
- Hurry, hurry.</i>

14
00:00:29,067 --> 00:00:31,500
<i>Mister Andy can't be
a partner or an investor.</i>

15
00:00:31,633 --> 00:00:33,600
<i>Why are you so mad
at Mister Andy?</i>

16
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:35,433
<i> He can't be trusted.</i>

17
00:00:35,567 --> 00:00:37,300
<i> I can't tell you why now,</i>

18
00:00:37,767 --> 00:00:40,533
<i>but I'm sure that
he can't be trusted.</i>

19
00:00:40,667 --> 00:00:42,233
<i>I'm telling you this
as your friend.</i>

20
00:00:42,700 --> 00:00:45,267
<i> For your sake and the hotel's.</i>

21
00:00:45,567 --> 00:00:47,233
<i> And for all of us!</i>

22
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:53,033
You shouldn't have
walked me home.

23
00:00:53,633 --> 00:00:55,967
I could've asked Joe
to drive me here.

24
00:00:58,500 --> 00:01:02,100
I'd have a better peace of mind
if I walked you home myself.

25
00:01:02,733 --> 00:01:04,867
And I'd have
a better peace of mind

26
00:01:05,000 --> 00:01:07,167
if I could make sure
that you're taking a rest.

27
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:10,000
It'll help heal
your wound faster.

28
00:01:10,367 --> 00:01:15,400
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYING]

29
00:01:15,533 --> 00:01:17,167
Are you worried about me?

30
00:01:21,567 --> 00:01:23,933
- [CHUCKLES]
- Well, yeah...

31
00:01:24,900 --> 00:01:28,133
Who wouldn't worry
after what you did?

32
00:01:31,400 --> 00:01:33,000
Well, it's a good thing, right?

33
00:01:34,933 --> 00:01:37,000
That you're worried about me?

34
00:01:43,467 --> 00:01:45,800
Let's talk about it inside.

35
00:01:48,033 --> 00:01:49,600
- Hey.
- Hey.

36
00:01:49,733 --> 00:01:51,100
- Hello.
- Hi.

37
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:55,300
- Oh!
- What happened?

38
00:01:56,067 --> 00:01:57,700
I got nauseous
from the size of your house.

39
00:01:57,833 --> 00:02:00,267
Oh, my god, Cheska!
Sorry about that.

40
00:02:01,233 --> 00:02:02,300
Let's go.

41
00:02:02,433 --> 00:02:04,233
[JADE LAUGHING]

42
00:02:06,367 --> 00:02:13,200
[THEME MUSIC PLAYING]

43
00:02:28,333 --> 00:02:35,233
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

44
00:02:50,367 --> 00:02:57,200
[THEME MUSIC CONTINUES]

45
00:03:07,567 --> 00:03:09,000
[CHESKA] Goodness!

46
00:03:09,500 --> 00:03:12,867
You rich people are so grand.

47
00:03:13,600 --> 00:03:16,100
Everything looks so fancy!

48
00:03:16,433 --> 00:03:18,367
This is so gorgeous!

49
00:03:19,467 --> 00:03:20,433
It's fine.

50
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,367
Nothing special.

51
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:24,833
What do you mean,
"nothing special"?

52
00:03:25,167 --> 00:03:26,333
It's gorgeous!

53
00:03:27,000 --> 00:03:29,200
Look at all those doors!

54
00:03:29,333 --> 00:03:31,700
That door over there.

55
00:03:31,833 --> 00:03:34,633
That's the size of the wall
in Kiko and my room!

56
00:03:34,767 --> 00:03:37,100
- Gosh!
- You're overreacting.

57
00:03:38,233 --> 00:03:39,367
Overreacting?

58
00:03:40,533 --> 00:03:42,200
I bet your house
is just as big.

59
00:03:42,333 --> 00:03:43,400
[CHUCKLES]

60
00:03:43,733 --> 00:03:46,233
Goodness, you two.

61
00:03:46,833 --> 00:03:49,900
You're just so used
to seeing fancy stuff like this

62
00:03:51,033 --> 00:03:54,400
that you don't get
to appreciate it anymore.

63
00:03:55,500 --> 00:03:57,667
I guess so.

64
00:04:00,633 --> 00:04:03,933
Or maybe I don't appreciate it
because it isn't special to me.

65
00:04:05,400 --> 00:04:10,233
[LIGHTHEARTED MUSIC PLAYING]

66
00:04:11,933 --> 00:04:13,667
Let's talk in my room.

67
00:04:14,500 --> 00:04:17,867
If my friends find out
I brought two girls in my room,

68
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:20,833
they're gonna be
so proud of me!

69
00:04:20,967 --> 00:04:23,667
We won't give in
to your fantasy.

70
00:04:23,800 --> 00:04:25,433
Come on, Trixie.
Let's have our own meeting.

71
00:04:25,567 --> 00:04:27,267
Wait, no!

72
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:29,700
Follow me. Hurry.

73
00:04:30,100 --> 00:04:31,133
This way.

74
00:04:32,633 --> 00:04:34,467
Grandma!

75
00:04:34,600 --> 00:04:36,700
Mm! [INHALES SHARPLY]

76
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,300
Oh, thank God, you came back.

77
00:04:40,867 --> 00:04:42,367
I've missed you, dear.

78
00:04:42,500 --> 00:04:45,167
I've missed you, too, Grandma.

79
00:04:45,700 --> 00:04:47,333
Is it true?

80
00:04:47,667 --> 00:04:49,167
It doesn't seem like it.

81
00:04:49,300 --> 00:04:51,000
If you really missed me,

82
00:04:51,133 --> 00:04:52,967
you would have come
to visit me sooner.

83
00:04:53,100 --> 00:04:54,133
Grandma...

84
00:04:54,433 --> 00:04:55,900
Just kidding!

85
00:04:56,033 --> 00:04:59,500
I'm so glad
you got to visit me again!

86
00:04:59,633 --> 00:05:00,833
[SIGHS]

87
00:05:01,000 --> 00:05:02,500
Will you be long?

88
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:06,300
I'm going to look for
some clothes you left behind.

89
00:05:06,433 --> 00:05:08,467
We came here on schedule.

90
00:05:08,600 --> 00:05:10,267
She really just wanted
to see you.

91
00:05:10,533 --> 00:05:12,800
- Mm-hm.
- Why so fast?

92
00:05:13,400 --> 00:05:16,367
Alright, then.
Let's make the most of it...

93
00:05:16,867 --> 00:05:19,600
- with<i> laing!
</i>- Oh!

94
00:05:19,733 --> 00:05:22,033
I have some in the freezer.

95
00:05:22,167 --> 00:05:24,233
I was planning
to send it to Gio.

96
00:05:24,367 --> 00:05:27,833
Come on. I'll also
cook you some grilled pork!

97
00:05:27,967 --> 00:05:29,800
Grandma, remember
what I said about pork?

98
00:05:30,167 --> 00:05:32,200
Well, it's not for me, is it?

99
00:05:32,333 --> 00:05:33,233
It's for Luna.

100
00:05:33,367 --> 00:05:34,967
You and your alibis.

101
00:05:35,133 --> 00:05:38,433
That's right!
The grilled pork is for me,

102
00:05:38,567 --> 00:05:39,967
not Grandma.

103
00:05:40,100 --> 00:05:42,200
- If you say so.
- [GRANDMA GIGGLES]

104
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,133
- Uh...
- [CHUCKLES]

105
00:05:44,467 --> 00:05:45,867
You must be hungry.

106
00:05:46,633 --> 00:05:49,100
Stay for dinner. I'll have
the maid cook something.

107
00:05:50,233 --> 00:05:52,233
[CHUCKLES] It's fine, Jade.
I'm going home.

108
00:05:52,367 --> 00:05:53,600
Come on.

109
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,300
That way, you can rest
when you get home.

110
00:05:57,367 --> 00:05:58,400
Please?

111
00:06:02,567 --> 00:06:03,467
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

112
00:06:07,833 --> 00:06:09,433
- [GROANS]
- Careful.

113
00:06:10,400 --> 00:06:15,267
[SOFT MUSIC PLAYS]

114
00:06:21,833 --> 00:06:25,033
I'm so used to Gio
not being here.

115
00:06:25,367 --> 00:06:29,500
But at least,
he tells me where he is.

116
00:06:33,233 --> 00:06:34,200
Dear.

117
00:06:35,767 --> 00:06:38,600
Uh, there's rice left
in the pot.

118
00:06:38,733 --> 00:06:40,633
[CHUCKLES] I'm fine, Grandma.

119
00:06:40,800 --> 00:06:42,700
This is enough.
I've eaten so much.

120
00:06:43,100 --> 00:06:46,267
Gio, does your hotel
serve bad food?

121
00:06:46,400 --> 00:06:50,133
Why doesn't Luna seem
to be eating well back there?

122
00:06:50,267 --> 00:06:52,033
She doesn't want
to eat so much.

123
00:06:52,167 --> 00:06:53,967
We all love Monette's cooking.

124
00:06:54,667 --> 00:06:57,133
That's true, Grandma.

125
00:06:57,267 --> 00:06:59,533
We have good food
in the hotel and at home.

126
00:07:00,033 --> 00:07:02,567
I just can't eat so much
because of--

127
00:07:09,500 --> 00:07:10,400
Hmm?

128
00:07:10,800 --> 00:07:12,300
B-because of work.

129
00:07:12,867 --> 00:07:14,967
- [LUNA CHUCKLES]
- Mm...

130
00:07:15,133 --> 00:07:17,167
Well, you're not in the hotel
or at home right now,

131
00:07:17,300 --> 00:07:20,100
so you can eat
as much as you want, okay?

132
00:07:20,367 --> 00:07:21,167
[GRANDMA] Mm.

133
00:07:21,300 --> 00:07:23,833
Yeah, you should listen to him.

134
00:07:23,967 --> 00:07:27,700
You should listen
to the people who love you.

135
00:07:27,833 --> 00:07:28,833
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

136
00:07:29,167 --> 00:07:32,300
[CALM MUSIC PLAYS]

137
00:07:32,733 --> 00:07:35,933
Gio, you can't deny it now.

138
00:07:36,300 --> 00:07:37,433
Grandma...

139
00:07:38,033 --> 00:07:39,900
[GRANDMA] Deserve!
[CLEARS THROAT]

140
00:07:40,033 --> 00:07:43,667
You deserve a sweet dessert!

141
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:45,500
Wait here, I'll take it out.

142
00:07:45,633 --> 00:07:48,967
The sweetest dessert!

143
00:07:49,733 --> 00:07:51,100
Eat up.

144
00:07:52,167 --> 00:07:57,233
[CALM MUSIC CONTINUES]

145
00:07:58,767 --> 00:08:00,500
Luna, you-- you have...

146
00:08:01,867 --> 00:08:03,033
What?

147
00:08:06,933 --> 00:08:09,500
- Something...
- Uh-- Oh.

148
00:08:10,067 --> 00:08:11,233
[CHUCKLES] The laing!

149
00:08:12,367 --> 00:08:13,533
I'm sorry!

150
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:17,233
Alright. How about now?

151
00:08:22,667 --> 00:08:23,667
It's all gone.

152
00:08:30,333 --> 00:08:34,300
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO VASQUEZ
PLAYING ON SPEAKER]

153
00:08:35,300 --> 00:08:37,633
Grandma, you said
you're getting dessert?

154
00:08:37,767 --> 00:08:39,167
Why is there music?

155
00:08:39,867 --> 00:08:42,600
The dessert that you deserve.

156
00:08:43,067 --> 00:08:45,000
This is it.

157
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:49,167
A very sweet sound trip
for you two.

158
00:08:49,533 --> 00:08:50,967
"Sound trip"?

159
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:54,033
Gio, did you teach Grandma
that word?

160
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,367
[GRANDMA HUMMING]

161
00:08:57,733 --> 00:08:59,067
[CHUCKLES]

162
00:08:59,567 --> 00:09:01,167
My god, Grandma.

163
00:09:02,267 --> 00:09:09,233
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO VASQUEZ
CONTINUES]

164
00:09:10,667 --> 00:09:11,800
No.

165
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:14,333
Come on.
Let's pretend we're in a bar.

166
00:09:15,067 --> 00:09:17,067
Why should we dance?

167
00:09:18,233 --> 00:09:19,467
Because there's music.

168
00:09:20,200 --> 00:09:21,367
And when there's music...

169
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,300
we dance.

170
00:09:29,533 --> 00:09:30,433
[CHUCKLES]

171
00:09:40,233 --> 00:09:47,233
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO VASQUEZ
CONTINUES]

172
00:09:52,833 --> 00:09:54,833
Guys, we really
can't go into that building.

173
00:09:54,967 --> 00:09:57,000
It's not safe.

174
00:09:57,133 --> 00:09:59,533
Yes, but that is the only way

175
00:09:59,667 --> 00:10:02,733
to know if Juan was taken there.

176
00:10:02,900 --> 00:10:06,000
I can't watch outside
to see when he'll leave.

177
00:10:06,133 --> 00:10:07,867
What if he was tied up?

178
00:10:08,000 --> 00:10:09,300
Or Juan wasn't there at all.

179
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:13,100
What? Didn't you see
the men guarding there?

180
00:10:13,233 --> 00:10:14,433
Unless you have
some ninja skills,

181
00:10:14,567 --> 00:10:16,533
you can't really get past them.

182
00:10:18,267 --> 00:10:19,267
[GROANS]

183
00:10:19,400 --> 00:10:20,767
[CHESKA] Well, hear me out.

184
00:10:20,900 --> 00:10:22,200
What if

185
00:10:22,333 --> 00:10:24,933
I'm going
to pretend I'm lost then...

186
00:10:25,067 --> 00:10:27,900
I'll ask the men there

187
00:10:28,033 --> 00:10:29,733
to help me reach my relatives.

188
00:10:29,867 --> 00:10:31,933
Whatever story I come up with.
I don't know.

189
00:10:32,067 --> 00:10:35,000
Then I'll pretend to need
to pee to get in there.

190
00:10:35,167 --> 00:10:36,800
[JUSTIN] No.

191
00:10:36,933 --> 00:10:38,700
No, no, no, no, no.

192
00:10:40,300 --> 00:10:42,267
That's dangerous.

193
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:44,533
What if they find out
you're just fooling them?

194
00:10:44,667 --> 00:10:46,367
You're tiny
and easy to get rid of.

195
00:10:47,567 --> 00:10:50,300
Don't put yourself
at risk, Cheska.

196
00:10:50,433 --> 00:10:51,500
Okay?

197
00:10:53,367 --> 00:10:54,467
[TONGUE CLICKS] Fine.

198
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:55,733
We'll think of another way,

199
00:10:55,867 --> 00:10:59,667
but what's important
is we're settled

200
00:10:59,800 --> 00:11:02,867
that the only way to see Juan
is to get in there.

201
00:11:03,000 --> 00:11:05,633
- Am I right?
- And you not having to pretend.

202
00:11:05,767 --> 00:11:06,967
And me not having to pretend.

203
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:08,833
Suggest more ideas, come on.

204
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:15,900
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING
OVER SPEAKERS]

205
00:11:21,867 --> 00:11:23,500
[BREATHES DEEPLY]

206
00:11:29,133 --> 00:11:30,467
Let's just stay here.

207
00:11:36,433 --> 00:11:37,700
Let's not go back.

208
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:53,100
My life's different now, Gio.

209
00:11:58,700 --> 00:12:00,000
I'm not Solenn anymore.

210
00:12:03,967 --> 00:12:05,533
I have a family
to take care of back home.

211
00:12:05,667 --> 00:12:07,100
I made a promise to Dad.

212
00:12:15,700 --> 00:12:17,100
Just until the song is done.

213
00:12:24,300 --> 00:12:31,067
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

214
00:12:46,167 --> 00:12:51,833
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

215
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:52,867
[MUSIC FADES]

216
00:12:53,000 --> 00:12:54,433
Three cups?

217
00:12:54,567 --> 00:12:57,167
Was that really
your regular rice serving?

218
00:12:57,300 --> 00:12:58,333
Yup.

219
00:12:58,467 --> 00:13:00,600
Sometimes, I could even do four.

220
00:13:00,733 --> 00:13:04,433
It depends on whether Dad grills
the fish we caught.

221
00:13:04,567 --> 00:13:05,767
- Wow.
- [CUTLERY CLANKS]

222
00:13:07,067 --> 00:13:10,067
'Wow'? That's not
something to be proud of.

223
00:13:10,200 --> 00:13:12,067
You know how big I used to be.

224
00:13:13,767 --> 00:13:15,300
But were you happy?

225
00:13:15,433 --> 00:13:16,600
[GENTLE MUSIC PLAYING]

226
00:13:16,733 --> 00:13:18,200
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY] Before?

227
00:13:19,867 --> 00:13:20,833
Of course.

228
00:13:22,633 --> 00:13:24,833
I just got sad

229
00:13:24,967 --> 00:13:26,933
when you didn't show up
because of how I looked.

230
00:13:28,433 --> 00:13:30,967
And we circled back to that.

231
00:13:31,100 --> 00:13:33,033
I'll just repeat myself.

232
00:13:34,600 --> 00:13:36,433
If I just look at
someone's physical appearance,

233
00:13:36,567 --> 00:13:39,267
then I shouldn't have
said yes to you at prom.

234
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:41,100
It's what's inside that matters.

235
00:13:44,400 --> 00:13:45,667
What about now?

236
00:13:47,033 --> 00:13:48,833
What do you mean?

237
00:13:48,967 --> 00:13:52,600
You said before that
you see past the physical.

238
00:13:52,733 --> 00:13:55,833
Does that mean
you do now because I'm fit?

239
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,167
You know,
that's not confidence anymore.

240
00:13:58,300 --> 00:13:59,167
You're being cocky.

241
00:13:59,300 --> 00:14:00,200
Wow.

242
00:14:00,333 --> 00:14:04,200
[BOTH CHUCKLE]

243
00:14:11,767 --> 00:14:13,267
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY] Sorry.

244
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:14,867
Sorry. [CLEARS THROAT]

245
00:14:16,400 --> 00:14:17,733
[CHUCKLES]

246
00:14:22,233 --> 00:14:23,600
You're smiling again.

247
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:29,233
You have no idea
what your smile does to me.

248
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:36,133
[SOFT MUSIC CONTINUES]

249
00:14:52,867 --> 00:14:54,833
[CHESKA] But I'm hungry.

250
00:14:54,967 --> 00:14:57,000
You didn't even offer me food.

251
00:14:57,133 --> 00:14:58,900
- [JADE] Cheska.
- Oh, you guys are still here.

252
00:15:00,467 --> 00:15:01,467
Justin

253
00:15:01,633 --> 00:15:02,867
[JUSTIN] There's still food.

254
00:15:04,467 --> 00:15:06,267
Miss, can you get one plate?

255
00:15:07,833 --> 00:15:09,033
[JADE] Eat up, guys.

256
00:15:09,167 --> 00:15:09,933
[CLEARS THROAT]

257
00:15:10,067 --> 00:15:11,367
I'm actually about to leave.

258
00:15:11,500 --> 00:15:13,000
Uh, we just had dinner.

259
00:15:13,133 --> 00:15:14,067
- [SNIFFLES]
- [CUTLERY CLANKS]

260
00:15:14,200 --> 00:15:16,033
Did Leon tell you
when he's going home?

261
00:15:17,000 --> 00:15:18,167
He hasn't.

262
00:15:19,433 --> 00:15:21,067
Yeah, where is Leon?

263
00:15:21,200 --> 00:15:24,633
[SOMBER MUSIC PLAYING]

264
00:15:24,767 --> 00:15:29,400
[MUSIC TURNS TENSE]

265
00:15:29,533 --> 00:15:33,367
[LEON GROANING]

266
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:46,167
[COUGHING]

267
00:15:50,767 --> 00:15:53,267
[PAPER RUSTLES]

268
00:16:07,567 --> 00:16:09,633
[GROANS, COUGHS]

269
00:16:15,400 --> 00:16:17,000
[TENSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

270
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:23,200
Jade, I think
I should get going.

271
00:16:24,333 --> 00:16:26,200
- I have to go.
- I'll see you off.

272
00:16:27,567 --> 00:16:28,500
Justin...

273
00:16:28,633 --> 00:16:31,133
- Cheska, I'll get going.
- [CHESKA] Take care!

274
00:16:31,267 --> 00:16:35,267
[FOOTSTEPS RETREATING]

275
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:42,467
[MELLOW MUSIC PLAYING]

276
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:45,633
Oh, thank you.

277
00:16:45,767 --> 00:16:48,100
Hey. Justin.

278
00:16:48,233 --> 00:16:49,167
Are they a thing?

279
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:53,733
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

280
00:16:53,867 --> 00:16:54,767
[CUTLERY CLINKING]

281
00:16:56,367 --> 00:16:57,467
[CUTLERY CLINKS]

282
00:16:58,900 --> 00:17:05,767
[MELLOW MUSIC CONTINUES]

283
00:17:06,733 --> 00:17:08,400
[CUTLERY CLINKS]

284
00:17:11,800 --> 00:17:13,433
Why are you looking
at me like that?

285
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,033
Nothing.

286
00:17:18,167 --> 00:17:19,800
Um...

287
00:17:19,933 --> 00:17:21,667
I just wanted to say that...

288
00:17:23,533 --> 00:17:26,300
I'm proud of what you're doing
for your family.

289
00:17:28,033 --> 00:17:28,933
Is that all?

290
00:17:30,300 --> 00:17:31,467
Yeah, that's all.

291
00:17:33,667 --> 00:17:34,500
[CUTLERY CLINKS]

292
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:35,733
Want some?

293
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,433
Just eat.

294
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:43,567
[TRIXIE] Wait.

295
00:17:43,700 --> 00:17:45,900
So, why are we planning
at your house?

296
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:48,433
We can't stay at the hotel.

297
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,800
You already know why.

298
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:53,633
We also can't stay outside.

299
00:17:54,633 --> 00:17:55,633
Unless...

300
00:17:55,767 --> 00:17:56,933
You have another place in mind.

301
00:17:58,367 --> 00:17:59,600
Justin.

302
00:18:00,800 --> 00:18:03,233
Is Edward
your sister's boyfriend?

303
00:18:03,367 --> 00:18:07,067
[MOROSE MUSIC PLAYING]

304
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:08,400
I'm not sure?

305
00:18:09,533 --> 00:18:12,500
But is Edward courting Jade?

306
00:18:15,600 --> 00:18:16,833
Yes?

307
00:18:16,967 --> 00:18:17,933
I don't know.

308
00:18:18,067 --> 00:18:22,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

309
00:18:22,533 --> 00:18:26,300
Why aren't you sure?
Your sister brings home a guy,

310
00:18:26,433 --> 00:18:27,500
and you don't care?

311
00:18:27,633 --> 00:18:30,033
- [TRIXIE CHUCKLING]
- [JUSTIN EXHALES]

312
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:33,367
Edward's a family friend,
so I'm used to seeing him here.

313
00:18:34,400 --> 00:18:35,700
But about their relationship...

314
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:39,033
I don't involve myself
with that.

315
00:18:42,500 --> 00:18:44,033
Why-- Why aren't you asking?

316
00:18:45,400 --> 00:18:47,400
Do we look close?

317
00:18:47,533 --> 00:18:50,333
Well, who are you
close with? Leon?

318
00:18:52,933 --> 00:18:53,867
Not either.

319
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:56,600
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

320
00:18:56,767 --> 00:18:57,667
[JUSTIN SIGHS]

321
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,400
I'm not close with any of them.

322
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:05,367
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

323
00:19:05,500 --> 00:19:06,767
It had always been that way.

324
00:19:08,967 --> 00:19:10,867
I'm used to not having allies
in this house.

325
00:19:13,333 --> 00:19:16,833
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

326
00:19:16,967 --> 00:19:17,900
That's sad.

327
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:20,433
[JUSTIN CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

328
00:19:20,567 --> 00:19:23,300
Why? Are you close with Kiko?

329
00:19:23,433 --> 00:19:25,200
Of course!

330
00:19:25,333 --> 00:19:27,033
We've only got each other,

331
00:19:27,167 --> 00:19:28,600
do you think we'd hate
one another?

332
00:19:28,767 --> 00:19:30,867
You really love each other?

333
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,367
Yeah. Why?

334
00:19:33,500 --> 00:19:36,467
Even though he is only
my half-brother...

335
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,933
We're best friends.

336
00:19:40,267 --> 00:19:43,233
Aren't you close
with Martin, too?

337
00:19:43,367 --> 00:19:45,267
Yeah, we're very close.

338
00:19:45,400 --> 00:19:47,700
I came to this island
because of him.

339
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:50,667
But we're not exactly the same
as you and Kiko.

340
00:19:50,800 --> 00:19:52,800
You're too messy.
[CHUCKLES]

341
00:19:53,900 --> 00:19:55,233
What if...

342
00:19:55,367 --> 00:19:57,733
I also get a half-brother?

343
00:19:57,867 --> 00:19:59,033
What?

344
00:19:59,167 --> 00:20:01,500
Your family's in enough mess,
you still want to add to that?

345
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:03,733
Why not?
So I could be like you.

346
00:20:04,967 --> 00:20:06,167
So I could have...

347
00:20:06,300 --> 00:20:07,500
...a sibling
who's my best friend.

348
00:20:07,633 --> 00:20:10,267
[MOROSE MUSIC CONTINUES]

349
00:20:10,400 --> 00:20:12,700
So, let's call it a night?
I'll drop you off.

350
00:20:13,667 --> 00:20:15,667
- [CHESKA] To the hotel?
- Just outside.

351
00:20:16,667 --> 00:20:18,700
- Just outside? [SCOFFS]
- There.

352
00:20:18,833 --> 00:20:20,067
This is why you're not close
with anyone.

353
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:21,300
Thanks.

354
00:20:21,433 --> 00:20:22,733
- You're too mean.
- [JUSTIN] Get out.

355
00:20:26,933 --> 00:20:28,967
What do you mean
there's nothing?

356
00:20:29,100 --> 00:20:31,100
That's impossible!

357
00:20:31,233 --> 00:20:35,167
[GOON]<i> There's nothing, sir.
</i> We already checked his car.

358
00:20:35,333 --> 00:20:37,200
Sandro's cellphone isn't there.

359
00:20:38,533 --> 00:20:40,600
I'm sure he has it.

360
00:20:41,967 --> 00:20:43,033
[ANDY BREATHES]

361
00:20:43,167 --> 00:20:45,167
Just keep a close eye
on Leon's every move.

362
00:20:45,300 --> 00:20:47,100
I'm sure
the truth will come out.

363
00:20:47,233 --> 00:20:49,100
[DOOR CREAKING]

364
00:20:49,233 --> 00:20:50,133
Dad?

365
00:20:50,267 --> 00:20:51,300
[DOOR SHUTS]

366
00:20:51,433 --> 00:20:53,200
- Hey.
- What's with Leon?

367
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,033
Uh, Leon, what about?

368
00:20:56,167 --> 00:20:57,500
- What about Leon?
- I heard

369
00:20:57,633 --> 00:21:00,167
you mentioned his name.
Did something happen

370
00:21:00,300 --> 00:21:01,867
- at the hotel?
- Oh, no.

371
00:21:02,000 --> 00:21:04,767
No, nothing like that.
It's just, um...

372
00:21:04,900 --> 00:21:06,500
Leon wasn't...

373
00:21:06,633 --> 00:21:09,633
He wasn't at the hotel
when I came by earlier,

374
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:12,867
which gives me the feeling...

375
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:16,433
...that Luna's the only one
who wants to partner with us.

376
00:21:16,567 --> 00:21:19,400
Really?
Leon said he didn't want to?

377
00:21:19,533 --> 00:21:23,500
Um, no. He didn't say
anything specific.

378
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:28,533
I just feel like
Luna's more welcoming...

379
00:21:28,667 --> 00:21:32,100
...so, all the more reason
you have to get Jade.

380
00:21:33,567 --> 00:21:34,900
Get Jade?

381
00:21:36,833 --> 00:21:39,367
Uh, in a sense that...

382
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:41,333
You will get her support.

383
00:21:41,500 --> 00:21:44,167
You know, so she can convince...

384
00:21:44,300 --> 00:21:47,133
...Leon and Justin
to still partner up with us.

385
00:21:48,667 --> 00:21:50,800
- Yeah.
- Ah, okay.

386
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:54,133
- Okay. Sure.
- Okay.

387
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,633
Sure, Dad.

388
00:21:56,767 --> 00:21:58,233
Alright.
Go ahead.

389
00:21:59,967 --> 00:22:00,767
[ANDY EXHALES]

390
00:22:00,900 --> 00:22:07,533
[UNSETTLING MUSIC PLAYING]

391
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,767
I'll send Grandma medicine
next week.

392
00:22:13,600 --> 00:22:14,933
Just send me her number.

393
00:22:15,100 --> 00:22:22,067
["TADHANA" BY SOFRONIO
VASQUEZ PLAYING]

394
00:22:37,167 --> 00:22:44,033
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

395
00:22:50,467 --> 00:22:51,433
[LUNA] Good night.

396
00:22:51,567 --> 00:22:58,667
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

397
00:23:13,567 --> 00:23:18,533
["TADHANA" CONTINUES]

398
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:21,000
<i> So close, bro.</i>

399
00:23:21,133 --> 00:23:22,167
<i> Are you confused?</i>

400
00:23:22,333 --> 00:23:25,167
<i>Are you more than friends
but less than lovers?</i>

401
00:23:25,300 --> 00:23:26,233
<i> If yes...</i>

402
00:23:26,367 --> 00:23:28,567
<i> that's a situationship.</i>

403
00:23:28,700 --> 00:23:30,600
<i>I'm looking for Sari.
Is she here?</i>

404
00:23:30,733 --> 00:23:32,433
<i> Sari is Martin's girlfriend.</i>

405
00:23:32,567 --> 00:23:34,067
<i> Is Leon at the hotel?</i>

406
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,467
<i>Is there a problem
with your brother?</i>

407
00:23:35,600 --> 00:23:36,900
He didn't come home last night.

408
00:23:37,033 --> 00:23:39,100
<i>As much as I want
to lock in Uncle Ronald,</i>

409
00:23:39,233 --> 00:23:41,133
<i>if we're going to have
problems internally...</i>

410
00:23:41,267 --> 00:23:43,033
<i>Then let's go with Andy
and avoid the hassle.</i>

411
00:23:43,167 --> 00:23:44,767
<i>- Why are you siding with him?
- Hey.</i>

412
00:23:44,900 --> 00:23:46,567
<i>We don't want
the Almazans fighting.</i>

413
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:48,000
<i>Shouldn't we want
the same for us, too?</i>
